Call Box exists to grow people. Our culture promotes a "work hard, play hard" mentality that offers growth opportunities for employees both inside and outside the office. We hire smart and ambitious doers and set them loose in an exciting and complex business environment where they will build, sell, and deploy Artificial Intelligence technology solutions. Our solutions attack one of the biggest business problems in existence today: the phone. 
We are looking for a highly motivated Junior Recruiter to join our Call Box team and help develop our talent pipeline, fill openings, and welcome new hires to the Call Box family. The responsibilities of a Junior Recruiter include developing job postings, crafting job descriptions, sourcing candidates through a variety of resources, conducting interviews, and managing our internal applicant tracking system. Hereâ€™s whatâ€™s really excitingâ€¦ you directly impact peopleâ€™s lives, help shape the Call Box culture, and provide the foundation for our long-term growth plans. 
What you will do: 
Attract suitable candidates through online employment forums, social media, events, etc. 
Source candidates using a variety of search methods to build a robust candidate pipeline 
Screen candidates by reviewing resumes and job applications, and perform phone screenings 
Promote the company's reputation, culture, and growth potential to prospective employees 
Develop job postings, job descriptions, and position requirements 
Act as the initial face of Calls Box by providing a seamless onboarding and new hire experience 
Stay abreast of recruiting trends and best practices 
Coordinate and manage the overall interview and selection process 
Ensure all screening, hiring, and selection is done in accordance with employment laws and regulations 
. Requirements:
 
Our Ideal Candidate: 
Ability to communicate effectively, both orally and in writing 
Demonstrated ability to establish effective and cooperative working relationships 
Urgency to exceed expectations and seek opportunities to continuously grow 
Excellent organizational and time management skills 
Working knowledge of applicant tracking and HRIS systems 
Working knowledge of interview techniques and applicant screening methods 
Familiarity with a wide variety of sourcing avenues 
Bachelor's Degree in Human Resources, Business Administration, or related field preferred 
